originalText.text:
I purchased a boudoir photo session as a wedding gift for my husband, but it was also very much something to do for myself as well. Like a lot of women, I was not always very confident about my body. But when I turned 30, I wanted to seriously work on learning to love myself more both inside and out. My session with Je Revele was a big part of that, and the entire experience was nothing short of amazing, with a lasting positive impact that continues to this day.

I had my hair and makeup done by Michelle, who has an true talent for putting people at ease (if you have the pre-boudoir butterflies) and bringing out their natural beauty. I loved her & her work so much I had her do the makeup for my wedding. Jessica was my photographer, who instantly made me feel very comfortable and beautiful. We laughed and had a fun time throughout the entire session. The results far exceeded my expectations, I've happily shown off my pictures to friends (never thought I'd do that!) who have purchased boudoir sessions of their own. I've also had the pleasure of meeting and keeping in contact with Natalie, who is a genuinely sweet person that I enjoy keeping in touch with. I cannot recommend Je Revele enough, and can't wait to use them when the time comes for our newborn portraits!

originalText.text:
I was referred to Je Revele a few years ago by the photographer Jerry Ghionis who photographed our wedding. I had asked at the time who the best photographer was to photograph my first child. He and his wife Melissa said hands down I had to talk to Natalie of Je Revele.

From the moment I first spoke to Natalie, she was great! We scheduled a shoot every two months for my daughters first year, as well her baptism. Each and every time, Natalie delivered the most breathtaking images. She had this amazing ability to draw out the best in my child and capture the moment beautifully. So when my husband and I had our second child a little over a year later, I couldn't wait to have Je Revele photograph our son.

I highly recommend Je Revele to everyone ! They are more than just photographers...they are artists.

originalText.text: From the moment I booked my photography session with Je Revele I knew that it was going to be something special.  I wanted to have boudoir photos taken as a gift for my husband but what I got was so much more.  Everyone I spoke to was always very professional and courteous and so easy to talk to that I never even felt nervous.  The staff was so friendly but even beyond that, they created an atmosphere that just put me at ease.  It was such a treat to take the day and have my hair and makeup done and have these very special photos taken that I can't stop admiring.  I booked with Je Revele because I have never seen such beautiful photography in my life.  I can't wait to go back for family photos.

originalText.text: My experience with Je Revele Fine Art Photography was amazing as I had the fortunate opportunity to meet Natalie and her wonderful team.  I always wanted to have my pictures done however I did not want them to look like something that you normally see (commercial, boring, that "already been done" look).  I feel the team brought the creativity to the table; from hair and make up to Natalie's vision behind the camera.  She made the entire experience amazing each step of the way (from the phone interview, to picture day, through picking what I wanted in my amazing album).  I feel that it was a great experience and I most definitely look forward to doing it again! Regardless if the pictures are family, babies, boudoir, or with dogs, the experience is professional, creative, and fun.  The work is excellent and simply artistic.  If I could give this review more than five stars, I would.

originalText.text:
My husband and I are both very happy with all the photos Natalie took for our new born baby. The photo shoot experience was fantastic. As a first time parent, we were quite nervous but she taught us great advices and tricks to keep our baby clam. (She is a mother of three children! She knows what to do!)

I highly recommend that you use their hair and makeup service. It is such a treat to get your hair and makeup done by a professional after giving a birth.

After the photo shoot, they invited us back to their studio to review all the photos. It was very difficult to narrow down, because we loved them all!!!!!
Their portraits are extremely high quality and worth every penny. They will last for years and years and I can't wait to show them to my son's future wife to be:)
